&quot;My queen!&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 747<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/03 6:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Old Times and Old Ways resurface</span><hr size=1> The voice caught Hippolyte off guard.  And tho the term was one she was used to...it felt odd to be called it after her long winter dissappearance.  Hippolyte walked away from the small hut she was working on and smiled.  Quickly her arms moved up in a salute as she knocked her bracer's together.  &quot;Lysia!&quot;  She walked over to one who had always been so strong and loyal to her thru the years.  Lysia had always kept to the back of the tribe...behind Hippolyte.  Not always noticed by the others.  But, Hipp always knew she was there.  &quot;I should not be surprised that you found me.&quot; <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

