<br>
 That was how it had started, of course. In wolf form Dawn had felt the need of her Queen, the urge that her Queen.. her first Queen was in need of help, in need of strong amazons, assassins, warriors, women that could help those whom had always been the ones they vowed to save. In the woods Dawn had headed and with midnight black fur pressed into the scent and feel the forest creatures, she began tracking.<br>
<br>
 It had taken merely, hours, and the emotions and feelings of Hippolyte had become more apparent to the wolf, and she knew the camp site Hipp had chosen wasn't far off. But, finding it was always more easier than approaching it; Dawn felt the energy of the two freightened women, and an animal wandering into the camp site wouldn't be making things easier.<br>
<br>
 But with the arrival of another Themiscryan, Dawn took her chances of running into the Queen.<br>
<br>
 Simply as the sun began to set, the dark creature curled its body around trees, and closer and closer to the campfire. And once no one paid attention to the outer limits of said camp fire.. on forepaws of fur, the assassin crawled. <br>
<br>
