&quot;I would like to set some nonlethal traps... if they catch a man we can kill him later, but it won't harm the women.&quot;  She preferred more direct methods, but powerful though they were they simply didn't have the numbers - yet - to patrol as tightly as she would like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 435<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Preparing.</span><hr size=1>  Dawn pulled the swords from the ground, and back to her sides and her back. The look, that look that clued all into her cynicism, shown brightly in the light of the coming morning and end of the evening. This was a mentality and prepartion she could easily tap into.<br>
<br>
 A simple grin slid across her visage, as Hippolyte spoke of the beasts. Dawn was a true beast, taking, and mastering the forms of any creature in the forest, and molding and creating its abilities into both her instinctive forms, and her human forms. This was more than just childs play, this was her hunt, this was more than being a man-slayer, this was being an assassin.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Kill with no remorse?&quot;<br>
<br>
 Blonde brow, rose above a what seemed to be a flowing pool of emerald, as Dawn kneeled, tightening and lacing her black elven boots, shifting her daggers and scabbards to the outside of her ankles and calves for an easier access.<br>
<br>
 Emeralds glanced to the two women Hippolyte had saved, and she studied them for a moment. This would be all to simple, in Dawn's eyes.<br>
<br>
 Being an amazon was just like being a tiger, or a wolf, to Dawn. It was fighting for these types of causes that made her stay, made her ignore the rights of the men around her. As a mother, she wanted her daughter to see the world the amazons created and if fighting for that, was what she needed to do to keep it around, she would. As an assassin, she was blood thirsty, hungry for the hunt, hungry for the blood that danced over her flesh; men were simple targets in that world. As a warrior, it was a fight and any fight that she could win she would take. Most importantly, as Dawn, as Ares chosen, as an immortal women, this was her world, this was what she lived for. Die or die by Dawn's hand, it was simple, it was method like, and it was truth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#993300>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#993300> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66>Anatolia / Ancient Turkey </a> <font color=#993300> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#993300> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

